<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call pthread_setcanceltype(PTHREAD_CANCEL_DEFERRED, &old_type) causes the previous cancel type to be stored into old_type, but old_type is never read or used later in the function or elsewhere. The write into old_type (the output parameter) is therefore an operation whose removal (e.g. passing NULL instead) would not affect observable program behaviour, so it constitutes dead code.
</scenario>
